extends java.lang.Object
    http://leetcode.com/onlinejudge#question_51

    The n-queens puzzle is the problem of placing n queens on an nxn chessboard such that no two queens attack each other.

    Given an integer n, return all distinct solutions to the n-queens puzzle.

    Each solution contains a distinct board configuration of the n-queens' placement, where 'Q' and '.' both indicate a queen and an empty space respectively.

    For example, There exist two distinct solutions to the 4-queens puzzle:

    [ [".Q..", // Solution 1 "...Q", "Q...", "..Q."],

    ["..Q.", // Solution 2 "Q...", "...Q", ".Q.."] ]

    Good articles: http://polythinking.wordpress.com/2013/02/27/leetcoden-queens-i-and-ii/ http://discuss.leetcode.com/questions/229/n-queens http://blog.unieagle.net/2012/10/16/leetcode%E9%A2%98%E7%9B%AE%EF%BC%9An-queens%EF%BC%8C%E5%9B%9E%E6%BA%AF/ http://gongxuns.blogspot.com/2012/12/leetcoden-queens.html http://www.matrix67.com/blog/archives/266
